# frontend.mdc — Frontend Build Specification

Frontend work must reference:
- The canonical directory structure defined in `.agents/folders.mdc`
- The Frontend Plan Playbook (`06-frontend-plan.md`)
- Global rules in `.cursorrules`

No exceptions.

---

## 1. Responsibilities

- UI/UX implementation  
- View-state + routing  
- Client-side business logic  
- API integration with backend  
- Component-level test coverage  
- Fidelity to design system + PRD

---

## 2. Frontend Phases (From Playbook 06)

### **Phase 1 — Scaffold**
- Initialise NextJS app aligned with folder structure  
- Create base layout system  
- Set up design tokens + global theme  
- Configure testing (Vitest/Jest + React Testing Library + Playwright)

### **Phase 2 — Core Views & State**
- Implement core pages  
- Establish API client layer  
- Create domain-level components  
- Match PRD acceptance criteria

### **Phase 3 — Feature Implementation**
- Build feature modules  
- Implement complex interactions  
- Add error/boundary components  
- Expand tests

### **Phase 4 — Integration & UX Polish**
- Integrate backend endpoints  
- Connect observability hooks  
- Final visual polish and animation rules  
- Full E2E tests

---

## 3. Constraints

- No structural duplication; folder tree is inherited from folders.mdc  
- Every view must map to a PRD feature section  
- Component library changes require update to architecture.md